Building dynamic web objects using OpenCPU


With OpenCPU you can use R as a data source for JavaScript objects (e.g.charts). The structure is as follows:

  1. You have a server running OpenCPU, R and RStudio. See this tutorial for instructions. My server runs here.
  2. The library folder of R contains packages with functions that can be accessed as an API.
  3. You can add users to the server who can build their own packages with their own functions.
  4. The functions in the package can be accessed via a server url. Ending it with /json returns a json file.

  5. This json file can be used as input for a JavaScript object, for instance a chart. Source code: 

    <style>
    .bar {
        fill: steelblue;
    }
    .bar:hover {
        fill: brown;
    }
    .axis {
        font: 10px sans-serif;
    }
    .axis path,
    .axis line {
        fill: none;
        stroke: #000;
        shape-rendering: crispEdges;
    }
</style>
<script type="text/javascript" src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.js"></script>
<script src="http://d3js.org/d3.v3.min.js"></script>
<script align="center">
    //When Document is Ready
    $(function() {
        //This part prepares the url string
        var resultsUrlPrefix = "http://ec2-34-252-17-179.eu-west-1.compute.amazonaws.com",
            url = resultsUrlPrefix + "/ocpu//user/rstudio/library/hellorobert/R/dataTest";
        //The following makes posts the url to the opencpu server on AWS and
        //concatenates the reply into a result link
        $.post(url,
                function(data) {

                    var statResultsLink = resultsUrlPrefix + data.toString().match(/.+\/.val/m) + "\/json";
                    $("#json1").attr("href", statResultsLink)

                    // Build chart (d3.js)
                    // set the dimensions of the canvas
                    var margin = {
                            top: 20,
                            right: 20,
                            bottom: 70,
                            left: 200
                        },
                        width = 600 - margin.left - margin.right,
                        height = 300 - margin.top - margin.bottom;


                    // set the ranges
                    var x = d3.scale.ordinal().rangeRoundBands([0, width], .05);

                    var y = d3.scale.linear().range([height, 0]);

                    // define the axis
                    var xAxis = d3.svg.axis()
                        .scale(x)
                        .orient("bottom")


                    var yAxis = d3.svg.axis()
                        .scale(y)
                        .orient("left")
                        .ticks(10);


                    // add the SVG element
                    var svg = d3.select("body").append("svg")
                        .attr("width", width + margin.left + margin.right)
                        .attr("height", height + margin.top + margin.bottom)
                        .append("g")
                        .attr("transform",
                            "translate(" + margin.left + "," + margin.top + ")");


                    // load the data

                    d3.json(statResultsLink, function(error, data) {

                        data.forEach(function(d) {
                            d.namen = d.namen;
                            d.leeftijd = +d.leeftijd;
                        });

                        // scale the range of the data
                        x.domain(data.map(function(d) {
                            return d.namen;
                        }));
                        y.domain([0, d3.max(data, function(d) {
                            return d.leeftijd;
                        })]);

                        // add axis
                        svg.append("g")
                            .attr("class", "x axis")
                            .attr("transform", "translate(0," + height + ")")
                            .call(xAxis)
                            .selectAll("text")
                            .style("text-anchor", "end")
                            .attr("dx", "-.8em")
                            .attr("dy", "-.55em")
                            .attr("transform", "rotate(-90)");

                        svg.append("g")
                            .attr("class", "y axis")
                            .call(yAxis)
                            .append("text")
                            .attr("transform", "rotate(-90)")
                            .attr("y", 5)
                            .attr("dy", ".71em")
                            .style("text-anchor", "end")
                            .text("Leeftijd");


                        // Add bar chart
                        svg.selectAll("bar")
                            .data(data)
                            .enter().append("rect")
                            .attr("class", "bar")
                            .attr("x", function(d) {
                                return x(d.namen);
                            })
                            .attr("width", x.rangeBand())
                            .attr("y", function(d) {
                                return y(d.leeftijd);
                            })
                            .attr("height", function(d) {
                                return height - y(d.leeftijd);
                            });

                    });

                })
            .error(function(jqXHR, status, error) {
                alert(jqXHR.responseText);
            });
    });
</script>
